 Hill New South Wales.jpg\n| image_size  = 300px\n| caption     = The Dunc Gray Velodrome\n| venues      = [[Western Sydney Parklands]]<br>[[Sydney]] and surrounding area<br>[[Dunc Gray Velodrome]]\n| date        = 16 September&nbsp;- 20 September\n| competitors = 462\n| nations     = 55\n| prev        = [[cycling at the 1996 Summer Olympics|1996]]\n| next        = [[cycling at the 2004 Summer Olympics|2004]]\n}}\n'''At the [[2000 Summer Olympics]]''', 3 different [[bicycle racing]] disciplines were contested: [[Road bicycle racing|Road cycling]], [[track cycling]], and [[mountain biking]].<ref name=\"SR\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/2000/CYC/ |title=Cycling at the 2000 Sydney Summer Games |work=Sports Reference |accessdate=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Road cycling==\n{| {{MedalistTable|type=Event}}\n|-\n| Men's road race<br>{{DetailsLink|Cycling at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's individual road race}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Jan Ullrich]]|GER|2000 Summer}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Alexander Vinokourov]]|KAZ|2000 Summer}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Andreas Kl\u00f6den]]|GER|2000 Summer}}\n|-\n| Men's time trial<br>{{DetailsLink|Cycling at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's road time trial}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Viatcheslav Ekimov]]|RUS|2000 Summer}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Jan Ullrich]]|GER|2000 Summer}}\n|Vacated<ref>[http://www.olympic.org/news/ioc-statement-on-lance-armstrong/188433 IOC statement], January 17, 2013</ref>\n|-\n| Women's road race<br>{{DetailsLink|Cycling at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's individual road race}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Leontien Zijlaard]]|NED|2000 Summer}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Hanka Kupfernagel]]|GER|2000 Summer}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Diana \u017dili\u016bt\u0117]]|LTU|2000 Summer}}\n|-\n| Women's time trial<br>{{DetailsLink|Cycling at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's road time trial}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Leontien Zijlaard]]|NED|2000 Summer}}\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Mari Holden]]|USA|